@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Architecture & AI Insights";
}

<link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap-icons@1.11.1/font/bootstrap-icons.css">

<div class="container mt-5 pb-5">
    <div class="text-center mb-5">
        <h1 class="display-4 fw-bold text-primary">Software Engineering & LLM</h1>
        <p class="lead">Merging Google Gemini's reasoning with Clean Architecture principles.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="card border-0 shadow-sm mb-5 bg-light">
        <div class="card-body p-4">
            <h4 class="fw-bold mb-4 text-center"><i class="bi bi-lightning-charge-fill text-warning"></i> AI Extraction Examples</h4>
            <div class="row g-4">
                <div class="col-md-4">
                    <div class="p-3 bg-white rounded shadow-sm h-100">
                        <span class="badge bg-secondary mb-2">A. Sparse Query</span>
                        <p class="small text-muted"><em>"dickens, tale two cities"</em></p>
                        <hr>
                        <p class="small mb-0"><strong>AI Logic:</strong> Identifies missing prepositions and completes the title to "A Tale of Two Cities".</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-4">
                    <div class="p-3 bg-white rounded shadow-sm h-100">
                        <span class="badge bg-danger mb-2">B. Noisy / Dense</span>
                        <p class="small text-muted"><em>"Tolkien Hobbit Illustrated Deluxe 1937"</em></p>
                        <hr>
                        <p class="small mb-0"><strong>AI Logic:</strong> Strips "Illustrated", "Deluxe", and "1937" to find the base book entity.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-4">
                    <div class="p-3 bg-white rounded shadow-sm h-100">
                        <span class="badge bg-info text-dark mb-2">C. Ambiguous / Clues</span>
                        <p class="small text-muted"><em>"Mark Huckleberry" or "Austen Bennet"</em></p>
                        <hr>
                        <p class="small mb-0"><strong>AI Logic:</strong> Reasons that "Mark" refers to Twain and "Huckleberry" to the title Finn.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row g-4">
        <div class="col-md-7">
            <div class="card h-100 border-0 shadow-sm">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h5 class="fw-bold text-primary mb-3"><i class="bi bi-code-square"></i> Where is the magic?</h5>
                    <div class="list-group list-group-flush">
                        <div class="list-group-item px-0">
                            <strong><span class="text-primary">LLM & Blob Logic:</span></strong> Located in <code>Infrastructure/AI/GeminiAiExtractionService.cs</code>. It uses System.Text.Json to turn raw blobs into structured DTOs.
                        </div>
                        <div class="list-group-item px-0">
                            <strong><span class="text-success">SOLID (OCP/LSP):</span></strong> Located in <code>Domain/Matching/</code>. You can add new search strategies (e.g., By Genre) without touching the core UseCase.
                        </div>
                        <div class="list-group-item px-0">
                            <strong><span class="text-warning text-dark">SOLID (SRP/DIP):</span></strong> Located in <code>Application/UseCases/</code>. Each class has one job, and they rely on Interfaces (Abstractions) rather than concrete APIs.
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="col-md-5">
            <div class="card h-100 border-0 shadow-sm bg-dark text-white text-center">
                <div class="card-body d-flex flex-column justify-content-center">
                    <h5 class="card-title opacity-75">Quality Assurance</h5>
                    <div class="display-1 fw-bold text-success">90%</div>
                    <p class="text-muted">Unit Test Coverage</p>
                    <div class="progress mx-auto w-75" style="height: 10px;">
                        <div class="progress-bar bg-success" style="width: 90.6%"></div>
                    </div>
                    <small class="mt-3 text-muted">Powered by xUnit & Moq</small>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row mt-5">
        <div class="col-12">
            <div class="card border-0 shadow-sm p-4">
                <h4 class="fw-bold mb-4">Enterprise Architecture: Clean MVC</h4>
                <div class="row align-items-center">
                    <div class="col-md-6 text-center border-end">
                        <h6 class="text-danger">Traditional MVC ("Fat" Controller)</h6>
                        <p class="small">The Controller talks directly to the DB and handles all logic. This is hard to maintain and impossible to test without a database.</p>
                        <div class="p-2 bg-light rounded font-monospace small">Controller ➔ Database</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-md-6 text-center">
                        <h6 class="text-success">Our Clean Approach (Decoupled)</h6>
                        <p class="small">The Controller is "slim"—it only delegates work to UseCases. Logic is portable and protected inside the Domain Core.</p>
                        <div class="p-2 bg-light rounded font-monospace small">UI ➔ UseCase ➔ Domain ➔ API</div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row mt-5">
        <div class="col-12">
            <h4 class="fw-bold"><i class="bi bi-journal-text"></i> Technical Glossary</h4>
            <div class="row mt-3 g-3">
                <div class="col-md-4">
                    <div class="p-3 border rounded h-100">
                        <span class="badge bg-primary mb-2">Blob</span>
                        <p class="small mb-0"><strong>Unstructured Data:</strong> A chunk of raw text. In this project, it's the "messy" input the user types before the AI cleans it.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-4">
                    <div class="p-3 border rounded h-100">
                        <span class="badge bg-primary mb-2">LLM</span>
                        <p class="small mb-0"><strong>Gemini 3 Flash:</strong> The Large Language Model used as a <em>Semantic Reasoner</em> to extract intent from the Blob.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-4">
                    <div class="p-3 border rounded h-100">
                        <span class="badge bg-primary mb-2">Strategy Pattern</span>
                        <p class="small mb-0">A design pattern used to decide the best "Match" criteria (Exact, Fuzzy, or Contributor) at runtime.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>